                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p32n5010h/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>was expedient or not for fulfilling those duties and if it was<lb/>\n                                        decided in the affirmative then to revert to steps for<lb/>\n                                        inducing the congregations to take the matter into\n                                        their<lb/> hands and found the Union, and it would belong to\n                                        the<lb/> Body appointed to carry out its objects to promote\n                                                  <add>?</add><lb/> to fulfill the duties. I cannot\n                                        say I understand in what<lb/> light the proposed meeting is\n                                        to be viewed. By the circular<lb/> and what some here say it\n                                        would appear it is to form<lb/> the Union at once and\n                                        proceed to legislate upon measures<lb/> still this does not\n                                        appear possible if I am rightly informed<lb/> that no\n                                        sending the delegates the congregation mean nothing<lb/> but\n                                        that they should have representatives at a meeting to\n                                        be<lb/> purely of a suggestive and <sic>advisary</sic>\n                                        character and not at<lb/> all legislative. With the crude\n                                        notions of some and the<lb/> small intelligence evinced by\n                                        others how to handle a measure<lb/> so important as a union\n                                        of the congregations, I shall regret<lb/> but certainly\n                                        shall not be surprised that the whole prove<lb/> a failure I\n                                        remain</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Revd Sir</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(2)\">Yrs. very truly</p>\n                              <p>\n                                        <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>\n                                        <hi rend=\"indent(3)\">\n                                                  <persName role=\"author\">A A. Lindo</persName>\n                                        </hi>\n                              </p>\n                              <p>I have just discovered an error in the second line of the<lb/>\n                                        concluding paragraph of my letter 2. page 612 of the<lb/>\n                                        occident for <date>march</date>, the word “Spiritual” having\n                                        been<lb/> substituted for “perpetual” which I will thank you\n                                        to take<lb/> on early opportunity to notice. Yrs <persName\n                                                  role=\"author\">AAL</persName></p>\n                              <div>\n                                        <p>\n                                                  <ref target=\"Occident_PDFs/Occ_7_4.pdf\">The above\n                                                  text refers to Occident Volume 7 No. 4 pages 203\n                                                  through 208. Click here to view.</ref>\n                                        </p>\n                                        <p>\n                                                  <ref target=\"Occident_PDFs/Occ_6_12.pdf\">The above\n                                                  text also refers to Occident Volume 6 No. 12 pages\n                                                  604 through 612. Click here to view.</ref>\n                                        </p>\n                              </div>\n                    </body>\n          </text>\n</TEI>"
                  },
